FireBase
React
Create react app (to start the project)
JSX - > kinda like HTML + JavaScript
Material UI -> Google components (https://material-ui.com/pt/)
ES7 React/Redux/GraphQL/React-Native snippets -> Extension creates the code for the components
  rfce -> create base code for components (react function component with export rfce)


Comandos:
To crate the base for the app
- npx create-react-app 'App name' 

Install FireBase IN OUR MACHINE (ONLY ONCE)
npm install -g firebase-tools

Login to FireBase (Be carefull with permissions to run scripts https://docs.microsoft.com/pt-br/powershell/module/microsoft.powershell.core/about/about_execution_policies?view=powershell-7)
firebase login

Install Materail UI
npm install @material-ui/core

